cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with neural network models of language and investigates how an LSTM language model deals with lexical ambiguity in English. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves designing a method to probe hidden representations for information about words. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves natural language processing and modeling. It may also fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves the use of LSTM neural networks. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) as it involves the representation of words in context.
